1 AN ACT relating to workforce investment, making an appropriation therefor, and
2 declaring an emergency.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF SUBCHAPTER 12 OF KRS CHAPTER
5 154 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
6 As used in Sections 1 to 4 of this Act:
7 (1) "Authority" means the Kentucky Economic Development Authority;
8 (2) "Cabinet" means the Cabinet for Economic Development;
9 (3) "Eligible grant applicant" means a county or city governing body, or entity
10 organized under Kentucky law providing public services or a nonprofit charitable
11 organization organized under 26 U.S.C. sec. 501(c)(3) or (6) engaged in
12 economic development, workforce investment, talent development, or community
13 development;
14 (4) "Eligible household" means a group of one (1) or more individuals living
15 together within one (1) dwelling:
16 (a) Residing outside of Kentucky when applying for the program funds; and
17 (b) Having a household income of at least sixty thousand dollars ($60,000);
18 (5) "Eligible project" means a talent recruitment program established by an eligible
19 grant applicant that includes:
20 (a) A household goal; and
21 (b) A plan to relocate employees from outside Kentucky;
22 (6) "Fund" means the Kentucky Talent Recruitment Grant Program Fund;
23 (7) "Household goal" means the total number of households that a talent
24 recruitment program seeks to incentivize for relocating or committing to relocate
25 from outside Kentucky to a Kentucky locality;
26 (8) "Program" means the Kentucky Talent Recruitment Grant Program; and
27 (9) "Regional project" means an eligible project that is proposed by eligible grant
