UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1711
1 154 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
2 (1) Applications for the program shall include a talent recruitment program plan
3 from the eligible grant applicant containing:
4 (a) The total estimated cost of the program;
5 (b) The individual estimated costs associated with the program design,
6 administration, marketing, and relocation incentive initiatives;
7 (c) The household goal and the grant amount per household;
8 (d) The program's estimated state and local tax impact; and
9 (e) The program's estimated total economic impact.
10 (2) Eligible grant applicants shall contribute twenty percent (20%) of total talent
11 recruitment program costs. Applicant contributions may include local
12 investments and in-kind donations. For regional projects, one (1) or more of the
13 eligible grant applicants may combine to meet the twenty percent (20%) local
14 match.
15 (3) Previous applicants may present a subsequent application if they met the
16 household goal in their previous application.
17 (4) Each approved eligible grant applicant shall report semiannually to the cabinet
18 the following:
19 (a) The total number of households that received program funds;
20 (b) A summary of the grant applications received from the eligible grant
21 applicants and submitted to the cabinet, including the grant amounts
22 awarded to eligible households;
23 (c) The current balance of the program funds awarded to eligible grant
24 applicants; and
25 (d) Recommendations for legislation or policy actions needed to facilitate
26 greater receipt of grant funding to eligible grant applicants.
27 (5) If the grant recipient fails to comply with this section or uses the awarded funds
