UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1711
1 for any purpose other than an eligible project, the grant recipient shall forfeit and
2 be liable to the cabinet for the full award amount.
3 SECTION 4. A NEW SECTION OF SUBCHAPTER 12 OF KRS CHAPTER
4 154 IS CREATED TO READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) There is hereby established in the State Treasury a trust and agency account to be
6 known as the Kentucky Talent Recruitment Grant Program fund. The fund shall
7 consist of moneys received from state appropriations, gifts, grants, and federal
8 funds.
9 (2) The fund shall be administered by the cabinet.
10 (3) Amounts deposited in the fund shall be used for awarding eligible grant
11 applicants funding for eligible projects.
12 (4) Notwithstanding KRS 45.229, fund amounts not expended at the close of a fiscal
13 year shall not lapse but shall be carried forward into the next fiscal year.
14 Section 5. There is hereby appropriated General Fund moneys in the amount of
15 $2,500,000 in fiscal year 2026-2027 and $2,500,000 in fiscal year 2027-2028 to the
16 Economic Development budget unit for the Kentucky Talent Recruitment Grant Program.
17 Section 6. Whereas providing timely funding for workforce investment
18 initiatives in the Commonwealth is important for the citizens of this state, an emergency
19 is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its passage and approval by the
20 Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
